{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3000,"text":"Fifty years ago in the old Soviet Union,"},{"time":6000,"text":"a team of engineers was secretly moving a large object"},{"time":9000,"text":"through a desolate countryside."},{"time":12000,"text":"With it, they were hoping to capture the minds of people everywhere"},{"time":15000,"text":"by being the first to conquer outer space."},{"time":18000,"text":"The rocket was huge."},{"time":20000,"text":"And packed in its nose was a silver ball"},{"time":22000,"text":"with two radios inside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"On October 4, 1957, they launched their rocket."},{"time":29000,"text":"One of the Russian scientists wrote at the time:"},{"time":32000,"text":"\"We are about to create a new planet"},{"time":34000,"text":"that we will call Sputnik."},{"time":37000,"text":"In the olden days, explorers"},{"time":39000,"text":"like Vasco da Gama and Columbus"},{"time":42000,"text":"had the good fortune to open up the terrestrial globe."},{"time":46000,"text":"Now we have the good fortune to open up space."},{"time":49000,"text":"And it is for those in the future to envy us our joy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"You're watching snippets from \"Sputnik,\" my fifth documentary feature,"},{"time":58000,"text":"which is just about completed."},{"time":61000,"text":"It tells the story of Sputnik,"},{"time":63000,"text":"and the story of what happened to America as a result."},{"time":66000,"text":"For days after the launch,"},{"time":68000,"text":"Sputnik was a wonderful curiosity."},{"time":71000,"text":"A man-made moon visible by ordinary citizens,"},{"time":75000,"text":"it inspired awe and pride"},{"time":78000,"text":"that humans had finally launched an object into space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"But just three days later, on a day they called Red Monday,"},{"time":86000,"text":"the media and the politicians told us,"},{"time":89000,"text":"and we believed, that Sputnik was proof"},{"time":91000,"text":"that our enemy had beaten us"},{"time":93000,"text":"in science and technology,"},{"time":96000,"text":"and that they could now attack us with hydrogen bombs,"},{"time":99000,"text":"using their Sputnik rocket as an IBM missile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103000,"text":"All hell broke loose."},{"time":105000,"text":"Sputnik quickly became one of the three great shocks to hit America --"},{"time":109000,"text":"historians say the equal of Pearl Harbor or 9/11."},{"time":113000,"text":"It provoked the missile gap."},{"time":116000,"text":"It exploded an arms race."},{"time":119000,"text":"It began the space race."},{"time":122000,"text":"Within a year, Congress funded huge weapons increases,"},{"time":125000,"text":"and we went from 1,200 nuclear weapons"},{"time":128000,"text":"to 20,000."},{"time":130000,"text":"And the reactions to Sputnik went far beyond weapons increases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"For example, some here will remember"},{"time":136000,"text":"this day, June 1958,"},{"time":138000,"text":"the National Civil Defense Drill,"},{"time":140000,"text":"where tens of millions of people in 78 cities went underground."},{"time":144000,"text":"Or the Gallup Poll that showed that seven in 10 Americans"},{"time":147000,"text":"believed that a nuclear war would happen,"},{"time":150000,"text":"and that at least 50 percent of our population"},{"time":152000,"text":"was going to be killed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"But Sputnik provoked wonderful changes as well."},{"time":158000,"text":"For example, some in this room went to school on scholarship"},{"time":160000,"text":"because of Sputnik."},{"time":162000,"text":"Support for engineering, math and science --"},{"time":165000,"text":"education in general -- boomed."},{"time":168000,"text":"And Vint Cerf points out that Sputnik"},{"time":170000,"text":"led directly to ARPA, and the Internet,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and, of course, NASA."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175000,"text":"My feature documentary shows how a free society"},{"time":178000,"text":"can be stampeded by those who know how to use media."},{"time":181000,"text":"But it also shows how we can turn"},{"time":183000,"text":"what appears at first to be a bad situation,"},{"time":186000,"text":"into something that was overall very good for America."},{"time":190000,"text":"\"Sputnik\" will soon be released."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"In closing, I would like to take a moment to thank"},{"time":195000,"text":"one of my investors:"},{"time":197000,"text":"longtime TEDster, Jay Walker."},{"time":199000,"text":"And I'd like to thank you all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"(Applause)."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"Thank you, Chris."}]}]}